learning_outcomes.et:
Kursuse läbinu:
1) mõistab demokraatia ja valitsemisega seotud põhimõistete ajaloolist arengut ja ja tähtsust (nt võim, kogukond, vabadus, õigused, esindatus, õiglus, legitiimsus, võrdsus);
2) oskab ära tunda ja hinnata demokraatia ja valitsemise põhilisi avaliku eetika tunnuseid ja põhimõtteid (nt korruptsioon, vastutus, õigusriik);
3) oskab formuleerida ja esitada oma seisukohti demokraatia ja valitsemise normatiivsete aspektide kohta nii kirjalikult kui suuliselt.

description.et:
Participation in forums (reading responses) and seminars.
Criteria for assessing reading responses: 
a) clarity, precision and conciseness in summarising the argument (summary);
b) ability to find interesting angles or topics in the text (the quotation and short comment); 
c) ability to identify problematic and unclear aspects in the text, make connections (question). 
Altogether you can gain 14 points for reading responses (2 points each, 7 seminars). While students participating in a debate need not post any comments on readings, other students are asked to post a short position-taking in the forum. This should outline 3 main arguments for the position you support and should reveal your familiarity with reading materials. Altogether you can gain 6 points for such posts (2 points per debate, 3 debates). 
Active seminar discussions will be assessed according to the following criteria: 
a) ability to make connections between theory and practice; 
b) ability to present arguments, points of view and questions. 
Students' participation in seminars will be graded cumulatively (as a whole) (max 20 points).
